          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1637925199740-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Pat the <strong>chicken thighs </strong>dry with<strong> kitchen paper</strong> and season them on both sides with <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> seasoned chicken</strong>, skin-side down, and cook for 10 min or until the skins have browned and crisped</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
