    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>diced pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle of olive oil<strong> </strong>if it's looking a little dry!</p><p>Once starting to soften, add the <strong>fennel seeds</strong>, <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong>, (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) <strong>chopped tomato</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>olives</strong>, <strong>capers </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until the tomatoes are starting to break down</p>",
